node.title: NT records one new local case of COVID, Katherine to move from lockdown to lockout from midday
node.alt: Natasha Fyles at the Marrara testing clinic during lockdown in the NT.
node.description: Katherine will move from out of lockdown and into a lockout from 12pm today, after only one new local case of COVID-19 was recorded in the NT.
node.content: ["There has\u00a0been one new local case\u00a0of COVID-19 recorded in the Northern Territory in the past 24 hours.", "The case, which takes the total number of cases in the Territory outbreak to 53, is\u00a0a 50-year-old man who is a household contact of existing cases.", "NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles said the man had been at the Howard Springs quarantine\u00a0facility throughout his infectious period, meaning he posed\u00a0\"no risk\" to the community.", "She said that as a result of promising results in recent days, the\u00a0Katherine area would move from a lockdown into a lockout from 12pm today.", "More to come."]
